28/12/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police arrested 114 illegal immigrants Friday (December 26th), in separate operations in the western province of Aydin and the north-western province of Edirne, media reported on Saturday. The immigrants came from China, Somalia, Myanmar, Iraq and Afghanistan. They will be deported according to procedures.
Meanwhile in Greece, border guards in the north-western city of Kastoria arrested three Albanian illegal immigrants and a Greek national, who allegedly helped them enter Greece, media reported on Friday. (Anadolu news agency, NTV - 27/12/08; Kathimerini, ERT - 26/12/08) 
